d_t: Regarding the question asking number of votes to break a filibuster, I chose "51", since that is the result of the recent change. It used to be "60". I forget when the "nuclear option" was adopted. Last week? Wasn't sure when this survey was composed. At present, though, it's 51 votes.

I believe the question regarding the filibuster is a bit tricky. I'm not sure when you started this survey, so I said 60. However, the rules just changed, and I believe it now only requires a simple majority.
